Subject: obo:PBPKO_00218
Value: KD in PBPK modeling refers to the dissociation constant of a drug/chemical-receptor complex, which is a measure of the affinity of the drug/chemical for its target receptor. It affects the distribution and elimination of the drug/chemical in the body. The dissociation constant (KD) is defined as the ratio of the rate constants for the forward and reverse reactions of the drug/chemical-receptor complex.
